    {
      "paragraph_name": "REPOSITION-AUTHORIZATIONS",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph repositions the IMS cursor to a specific authorization detail segment (PAUTDTL1) based on the value of WS-AUTH-KEY-SAVE. It moves WS-AUTH-KEY-SAVE to PA-AUTHORIZATION-KEY and then executes a GNP (Get Next within Parent) call with a WHERE clause to retrieve the segment where PAUT9CTS matches PA-AUTHORIZATION-KEY. It moves the DIBSTAT value to IMS-RETURN-CODE. It then evaluates the IMS-RETURN-CODE. If the status is STATUS-OK, AUTHS-NOT-EOF is set to TRUE. If the status is SEGMENT-NOT-FOUND or END-OF-DB, AUTHS-EOF is set to TRUE. If the status is OTHER, it sets WS-ERR-FLG to 'Y', constructs an error message containing the IMS-RETURN-CODE, moves it to WS-MESSAGE, sets ACCTIDL to -1, and calls SEND-PAULST-SCREEN to display the error message.",
