    {
      "paragraph_name": "RETURN-TO-PREV-SCREEN",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph handles the return to the previous screen. It checks if CDEMO-TO-PROGRAM is LOW-VALUES or SPACES, and if so, it sets CDEMO-TO-PROGRAM to 'COSGN00C'. It then moves the current transaction ID (WS-CICS-TRANID) to CDEMO-FROM-TRANID, the program ID (WS-PGM-AUTH-SMRY) to CDEMO-FROM-PROGRAM, and ZEROS to CDEMO-PGM-CONTEXT. Finally, it performs a CICS XCTL to the program specified in CDEMO-TO-PROGRAM, passing the CARDDEMO-COMMAREA. This paragraph essentially transfers control to another program, likely the calling program, passing data through the COMMAREA. The paragraph consumes WS-CICS-TRANID, WS-PGM-AUTH-SMRY, CDEMO-TO-PROGRAM, and CARDDEMO-COMMAREA and calls the CDEMO-TO-PROGRAM via XCTL.",
