    {
      "paragraph_name": "SEND-PAULST-SCREEN",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph sends the COPAU0A screen to the terminal. It first checks if IMS-PSB-SCHD is true, and if so, it sets IMS-PSB-NOT-SCHD to true and performs a CICS SYNCPOINT. Then, it calls POPULATE-HEADER-INFO to populate the header information on the screen. It moves WS-MESSAGE to ERRMSGO of COPAU0AO. Finally, it checks the SEND-ERASE-YES flag. If it is true, it sends the map with the ERASE option, clearing the screen before displaying the data. Otherwise, it sends the map without the ERASE option, overlaying the new data on the existing screen. In both cases, the CURSOR option is used to position the cursor on the screen. The paragraph consumes IMS-PSB-SCHD, WS-MESSAGE, SEND-ERASE-YES, and COPAU0AO and calls POPULATE-HEADER-INFO.",
      "called_by": [
